# Quro Waitlist - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 waitlist application for Quro, using TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and SQLite.

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer async/await over promises
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow Next.js 14 App Router conventions

## File Structure
- `/app` - Next.js app router pages and layouts
- `/app/api` - API routes
- `/lib` - Utility functions and database logic
- `/public` - Static assets

## Database
- SQLite with better-sqlite3
- Database functions are in `/lib/db.ts`
- Never expose database queries in client components

## Security
- Admin routes require authentication
- Validate all user inputs
- Sanitize email addresses
- Use environment variables for secrets

## Testing
- Test email validation
- Test admin authentication
- Test database operations
- Test visitor tracking

